    <stitle>SINGLE SPEED REAR AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE - PINION ( Figure 15 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>PINION (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400815">Figure 15</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1400815" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400815" filename="../figg14/G1400815.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Pinion - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion cage mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400816">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400816" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400816" filename="../figg14/G1400816.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion and cage assembly from carrier housing. If difficulty is encountered in
                removing pinion assembly from carrier housing, place brass drift on inner end of pinion gear and tap
                lightly.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Retain shims for possible use during reassembly (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1400817">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1400817" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400817" filename="../figg14/G1400817.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Retain Shims</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount pinion assembly in a soft jawed vise or fixture. Holding yoke stationary, remove nut
                and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400818">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400818" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400818" filename="../figg14/G1400818.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Assembly In Vise</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the end yoke using a suitable puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400819">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400819" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400819" filename="../figg14/G1400819.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove End Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion gear from cage assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It may be necessary to tap outer end of pinion gear with a soft hammer. Replace pinion nut,
                        flush with end of pinion, so damage to threads does not occur.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Located between pinion bearings is a selective spacer, used for pinion bearing preload.
                Retain this spacer for possible use in reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400820">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400820" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400820" filename="../figg14/G1400820.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Selective Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove old pinion seal and discard. Always replace it with a new seal at time of
                reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift out outer pinion bearing cone.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove inner pinion bearing cup, using a suitable adapter and press or puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400821">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400821" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400821" filename="../figg14/G1400821.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Inner Pinion Bearing Cup</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not nick bearing bore.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove outer pinion bearing cup, using same procedure as Step 9.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion roller bearing from end of pinion (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400822">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400822" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400822" filename="../figg14/G1400822.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Pinion Roller Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Bearing must be shielded during removal to eliminate possible personal injury if bearing races
                        shatter.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove inner bearing cone from pinion gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400823">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400823" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400823" filename="../figg14/G1400823.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Inner Bearing Cone</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
